#. <section class="sutta" id="an3.65"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "an3.65:0.1"
msgid "Aṅguttara Nikāya 3"
msgstr "Numbered Discourses 3"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "an3.65:0.2"
msgid "7. Mahāvagga"
msgstr "7. The Great Chapter"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "an3.65:0.3"
msgid "65. Kesamuttisutta"
msgstr "65. Kālāma"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "an3.65:1.1"
msgid "Evaṃ me sutaṃ—​"
msgstr "So I have heard."

#. VAR: kesamuttaṃ → kesaputtaṃ (bj, s1-3, km, pts1)
msgctxt "an3.65:1.2"
msgid ""
"ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā kosalesu cārikaṃ caramāno mahatā bhikkhusaṃghena "
"saddhiṃ yena kesamuttaṃ nāma kālāmānaṃ nigamo tadavasari."
msgstr ""
"At one time the Buddha was wandering in the land of the Kosalans together "
"with a large Saṅgha of mendicants when he arrived at a town of the Kālāmas "
"named Kesamutta."

msgctxt "an3.65:1.3"
msgid "Assosuṃ kho kesamuttiyā kālāmā:"
msgstr "The Kālāmas of Kesamutta heard:"

msgctxt "an3.65:1.4"
msgid ""
"“samaṇo khalu, bho, gotamo sakyaputto sakyakulā pabbajito kesamuttaṃ "
"anuppatto."
msgstr ""
"“It seems the ascetic Gotama—a Sakyan, gone forth from a Sakyan family—has "
"arrived at Kesamutta."

msgctxt "an3.65:1.5"
msgid "Taṃ kho pana bhavantaṃ gotamaṃ evaṃ kalyāṇo kittisaddo abbhuggato:"
msgstr "He has this good reputation:"

msgctxt "an3.65:1.6"
msgid "‘itipi so bhagavā … pe …"
msgstr "‘That Blessed One is perfected, a fully awakened Buddha …’"

msgctxt "an3.65:1.7"
msgid "sādhu kho pana tathārūpānaṃ arahataṃ dassanaṃ hotī’”ti."
msgstr "It’s good to see such perfected ones.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "an3.65:2.1"
msgid ""
"Atha kho kesamuttiyā kālāmā yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkamiṃsu; upasaṅkamitvā "
"appekacce bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdiṃsu, appekacce bhagavatā "
"saddhiṃ sammodiṃsu, sammodanīyaṃ kathaṃ sāraṇīyaṃ vītisāretvā ekamantaṃ "
"nisīdiṃsu, appekacce yena bhagavā tenañjaliṃ paṇāmetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdiṃsu, "
"appekacce nāmagottaṃ sāvetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdiṃsu, appekacce tuṇhībhūtā "
"ekamantaṃ nisīdiṃsu. Ekamantaṃ nisinnā kho te kesamuttiyā kālāmā bhagavantaṃ "
"etadavocuṃ:"
msgstr ""
"Then the Kālāmas went up to the Buddha. Before sitting down to one side, "
"some bowed, some exchanged greetings and polite conversation, some held up "
"their joined palms toward the Buddha, some announced their name and clan, "
"while some kept silent. Seated to one side the Kālāmas said to the Buddha:"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pli1.189"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "an3.65:3.1"
msgid "“Santi, bhante, eke samaṇabrāhmaṇā kesamuttaṃ āgacchanti."
msgstr "“There are, sir, some ascetics and brahmins who come to Kesamutta."

#. VAR: parappavādaṃ → paravādaṃ (bj, s1-3)
#. VAR: paribhavanti omakkhiṃ → opapakkhiṃ (sī, syā1-3, kaṃ, pā1), omakkhikaṃ (ka-ma)
msgctxt "an3.65:3.2"
msgid ""
"Te sakaṃyeva vādaṃ dīpenti jotenti, parappavādaṃ pana khuṃsenti vambhenti "
"paribhavanti omakkhiṃ karonti."
msgstr ""
"They explain and promote only their own doctrine, while they attack, "
"badmouth, disparage, and smear the doctrines of others."

msgctxt "an3.65:3.3"
msgid "Aparepi, bhante, eke samaṇabrāhmaṇā kesamuttaṃ āgacchanti."
msgstr "Then some other ascetics and brahmins come to Kesamutta."

msgctxt "an3.65:3.4"
msgid ""
"Tepi sakaṃyeva vādaṃ dīpenti jotenti, parappavādaṃ pana khuṃsenti vambhenti "
"paribhavanti omakkhiṃ karonti."
msgstr ""
"They too explain and promote only their own doctrine, while they attack, "
"badmouth, disparage, and smear the doctrines of others."

msgctxt "an3.65:3.5"
msgid "Tesaṃ no, bhante, amhākaṃ hoteva kaṅkhā hoti vicikicchā:"
msgstr "So, sir, we’re doubting and uncertain:"

msgctxt "an3.65:3.6"
msgid "‘ko su nāma imesaṃ bhavataṃ samaṇabrāhmaṇānaṃ saccaṃ āha, ko musā’”ti?"
msgstr ""
"‘I wonder who of these respected ascetics and brahmins speaks the truth, and "
"who speaks falsehood?’”"

msgctxt "an3.65:3.7"
msgid "“Alañhi vo, kālāmā, kaṅkhituṃ alaṃ vicikicchituṃ."
msgstr "“It is enough, Kālāmas, for you to be doubting and uncertain."

#. VAR: Kaṅkhanīyeva pana → kaṅkhanīye ca pana (bj) | kaṅkhāniyeva pana (s1-3, pts1)
msgctxt "an3.65:3.8"
msgid "Kaṅkhanīyeva pana vo ṭhāne vicikicchā uppannā."
msgstr "Doubt has come up in you about an uncertain matter."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc4"></a>
msgctxt "an3.65:4.1"
msgid ""
"Etha tumhe, kālāmā, mā anussavena, mā paramparāya, mā itikirāya, mā "
"piṭakasampadānena, mā takkahetu, mā nayahetu, mā ākāraparivitakkena, mā "
"diṭṭhinijjhānakkhantiyā, mā bhabbarūpatāya, mā samaṇo no garūti."
msgstr ""
"Please, Kālāmas, don’t go by oral transmission, don’t go by lineage, don’t "
"go by testament, don’t go by canonical authority, don’t rely on logic, don’t "
"rely on inference, don’t go by reasoned contemplation, don’t go by the "
"acceptance of a view after consideration, don’t go by the appearance of "
"competence, and don’t think ‘The ascetic is our respected teacher.’"

msgctxt "an3.65:4.2"
msgid "Yadā tumhe, kālāmā, attanāva jāneyyātha:"
msgstr "But when you know for yourselves:"

#. VAR: samādinnā → samādiṇṇā (mr)
msgctxt "an3.65:4.3"
msgid ""
"‘ime dhammā akusalā, ime dhammā sāvajjā, ime dhammā viññugarahitā, ime "
"dhammā samattā samādinnā ahitāya dukkhāya saṃvattantī’ti, atha tumhe, "
"kālāmā, pajaheyyātha."
msgstr ""
"‘These things are unskillful, blameworthy, criticized by sensible people, "
"and when you undertake them, they lead to harm and suffering’, then you "
"should give them up."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc5"></a>
msgctxt "an3.65:5.1"
msgid "Taṃ kiṃ maññatha, kālāmā, "
msgstr "What do you think, Kālāmas? "

msgctxt "an3.65:5.2"
msgid ""
"lobho purisassa ajjhattaṃ uppajjamāno uppajjati hitāya vā ahitāya vā”ti?"
msgstr "Does greed come up in a person for their welfare or harm?”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc6"></a>
msgctxt "an3.65:6.1"
msgid "“Ahitāya, bhante”."
msgstr "“Harm, sir.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc7"></a>
#. VAR: tathattāya → tadatthāya (mr)
#. VAR: yaṃ sa → yaṃ tassa (mr)
msgctxt "an3.65:7.1"
msgid ""
"“Luddho panāyaṃ, kālāmā, purisapuggalo lobhena abhibhūto pariyādinnacitto "
"pāṇampi hanati, adinnampi ādiyati, paradārampi gacchati, musāpi bhaṇati, "
"parampi tathattāya samādapeti, yaṃ sa hoti dīgharattaṃ ahitāya dukkhāyā”ti."
msgstr ""
"“A greedy individual, overcome by greed, kills living creatures, steals, "
"commits adultery, lies, and encourages others to do the same. Is that for "
"their lasting harm and suffering?”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc8"></a>
msgctxt "an3.65:8.1"
msgid "“Evaṃ, bhante”."
msgstr "“Yes, sir.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc9"></a>
msgctxt "an3.65:9.1"
msgid "“Taṃ kiṃ maññatha, kālāmā, "
msgstr "“What do you think, Kālāmas? "

msgctxt "an3.65:9.2"
msgid "doso purisassa ajjhattaṃ uppajjamāno uppajjati hitāya vā ahitāya vā”ti?"
msgstr "Does hate come up in a person for their welfare or harm?”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc10"></a>
msgctxt "an3.65:10.1"
msgid "“Ahitāya, bhante”."
msgstr "“Harm, sir.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc11"></a>
#. VAR: hanati → hanti (bj, pts1)
msgctxt "an3.65:11.1"
msgid ""
"“Duṭṭho panāyaṃ, kālāmā, purisapuggalo dosena abhibhūto pariyādinnacitto "
"pāṇampi hanati, adinnampi ādiyati, paradārampi gacchati, musāpi bhaṇati, "
"parampi tathattāya samādapeti, yaṃ sa hoti dīgharattaṃ ahitāya dukkhāyā”ti."
msgstr ""
"“A hateful individual, overcome by hate, kills living creatures, steals, "
"commits adultery, lies, and encourages others to do the same. Is that for "
"their lasting harm and suffering?”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc12"></a>
msgctxt "an3.65:12.1"
msgid "“Evaṃ, bhante”."
msgstr "“Yes, sir.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc13"></a>
msgctxt "an3.65:13.1"
msgid "“Taṃ kiṃ maññatha, kālāmā, "
msgstr "“What do you think, Kālāmas? "

msgctxt "an3.65:13.2"
msgid "moho purisassa ajjhattaṃ uppajjamāno uppajjati hitāya vā ahitāya vā”ti?"
msgstr "Does delusion come up in a person for their welfare or harm?”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc14"></a>
msgctxt "an3.65:14.1"
msgid "“Ahitāya, bhante”."
msgstr "“Harm, sir.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pli1.190"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc15"></a>
msgctxt "an3.65:15.1"
msgid ""
"“Mūḷho panāyaṃ, kālāmā, purisapuggalo mohena abhibhūto pariyādinnacitto "
"pāṇampi hanati, adinnampi ādiyati, paradārampi gacchati, musāpi bhaṇati, "
"parampi tathattāya samādapeti, yaṃ sa hoti dīgharattaṃ ahitāya dukkhāyā”ti."
msgstr ""
"“A deluded individual, overcome by delusion, kills living creatures, steals, "
"commits adultery, lies, and encourages others to do the same. Is that for "
"their lasting harm and suffering?”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc16"></a>
msgctxt "an3.65:16.1"
msgid "“Evaṃ, bhante”."
msgstr "“Yes, sir.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc17"></a>
msgctxt "an3.65:17.1"
msgid "“Taṃ kiṃ maññatha, kālāmā, ime dhammā kusalā vā akusalā vā”ti?"
msgstr "“What do you think, Kālāmas, are these things skillful or unskillful?”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc18"></a>
msgctxt "an3.65:18.1"
msgid "“Akusalā, bhante”."
msgstr "“Unskillful, sir.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc19"></a>
msgctxt "an3.65:19.1"
msgid "“Sāvajjā vā anavajjā vā”ti?"
msgstr "“Blameworthy or blameless?”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc20"></a>
msgctxt "an3.65:20.1"
msgid "“Sāvajjā, bhante”."
msgstr "“Blameworthy, sir.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc21"></a>
msgctxt "an3.65:21.1"
msgid "“Viññugarahitā vā viññuppasatthā vā”ti?"
msgstr "“Criticized or praised by sensible people?”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc22"></a>
msgctxt "an3.65:22.1"
msgid "“Viññugarahitā, bhante”."
msgstr "“Criticized by sensible people, sir.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc23"></a>
msgctxt "an3.65:23.1"
msgid "“Samattā samādinnā ahitāya dukkhāya saṃvattanti, no vā?"
msgstr "“When you undertake them, do they lead to harm and suffering, or not?"

#. VAR: Kathaṃ vā → kathaṃ vā vo (?)
msgctxt "an3.65:23.2"
msgid "Kathaṃ vā ettha hotī”ti?"
msgstr "Or how do you see this?”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc24"></a>
msgctxt "an3.65:24.1"
msgid "“Samattā, bhante, samādinnā ahitāya dukkhāya saṃvattantīti."
msgstr "“When you undertake them, they lead to harm and suffering."

msgctxt "an3.65:24.2"
msgid "Evaṃ no ettha hotī”ti."
msgstr "That’s how we see it.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc25"></a>
#. VAR: avocumhā → avocumha (bj, s1-3, km, pts1)
msgctxt "an3.65:25.1"
msgid "“Iti kho, kālāmā, yaṃ taṃ avocumhā:"
msgstr "“So, Kālāmas, when we said:"

msgctxt "an3.65:25.2"
msgid "‘etha tumhe, kālāmā."
msgstr "‘Please,"

msgctxt "an3.65:25.3"
msgid ""
"Mā anussavena, mā paramparāya, mā itikirāya, mā piṭakasampadānena, mā "
"takkahetu, mā nayahetu, mā ākāraparivitakkena, mā diṭṭhinijjhānakkhantiyā, "
"mā bhabbarūpatāya, mā samaṇo no garūti."
msgstr ""
"don’t go by oral transmission, don’t go by lineage, don’t go by testament, "
"don’t go by canonical authority, don’t rely on logic, don’t rely on "
"inference, don’t go by reasoned contemplation, don’t go by the acceptance of "
"a view after consideration, don’t go by the appearance of competence, and "
"don’t think “The ascetic is our respected teacher.”"

msgctxt "an3.65:25.4"
msgid "Yadā tumhe kālāmā attanāva jāneyyātha:"
msgstr "But when you know for yourselves:"

msgctxt "an3.65:25.5"
msgid ""
"“ime dhammā akusalā, ime dhammā sāvajjā, ime dhammā viññugarahitā, ime "
"dhammā samattā samādinnā ahitāya dukkhāya saṃvattantīti, atha tumhe, kālāmā, "
"pajaheyyāthā”’ti, "
msgstr ""
"“These things are unskillful, blameworthy, criticized by sensible people, "
"and when you undertake them, they lead to harm and suffering”, then you "
"should give them up.’ "

msgctxt "an3.65:25.6"
msgid "iti yaṃ taṃ vuttaṃ, idametaṃ paṭicca vuttaṃ."
msgstr "That’s what I said, and this is why I said it."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc26"></a>
msgctxt "an3.65:26.1"
msgid ""
"Etha tumhe, kālāmā, mā anussavena, mā paramparāya, mā itikirāya, mā "
"piṭakasampadānena, mā takkahetu, mā nayahetu, mā ākāraparivitakkena, mā "
"diṭṭhinijjhānakkhantiyā, mā bhabbarūpatāya, mā samaṇo no garūti."
msgstr ""
"Please, Kālāmas, don’t go by oral transmission, don’t go by lineage, don’t "
"go by testament, don’t go by canonical authority, don’t rely on logic, don’t "
"rely on inference, don’t go by reasoned contemplation, don’t go by the "
"acceptance of a view after consideration, don’t go by the appearance of "
"competence, and don’t think ‘The ascetic is our respected teacher.’"

msgctxt "an3.65:26.2"
msgid "Yadā tumhe, kālāmā, attanāva jāneyyātha:"
msgstr "But when you know for yourselves:"

msgctxt "an3.65:26.3"
msgid ""
"‘ime dhammā kusalā, ime dhammā anavajjā, ime dhammā viññuppasatthā, ime "
"dhammā samattā samādinnā hitāya sukhāya saṃvattantī’ti, atha tumhe, kālāmā, "
"upasampajja vihareyyātha."
msgstr ""
"‘These things are skillful, blameless, praised by sensible people, and when "
"you undertake them, they lead to welfare and happiness’, then you should "
"acquire them and keep them."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc27"></a>
msgctxt "an3.65:27.1"
msgid "Taṃ kiṃ maññatha, kālāmā, "
msgstr "What do you think, Kālāmas? "

msgctxt "an3.65:27.2"
msgid ""
"alobho purisassa ajjhattaṃ uppajjamāno uppajjati hitāya vā ahitāya vā”ti?"
msgstr "Does contentment come up in a person for their welfare or harm?”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc28"></a>
msgctxt "an3.65:28.1"
msgid "“Hitāya, bhante”."
msgstr "“Welfare, sir.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pli1.191"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc29"></a>
msgctxt "an3.65:29.1"
msgid ""
"“Aluddho panāyaṃ, kālāmā, purisapuggalo lobhena anabhibhūto "
"apariyādinnacitto neva pāṇaṃ hanati, na adinnaṃ ādiyati, na paradāraṃ "
"gacchati, na musā bhaṇati, na parampi tathattāya samādapeti, yaṃ sa hoti "
"dīgharattaṃ hitāya sukhāyā”ti."
msgstr ""
"“An individual who is content, not overcome by greed, doesn’t kill living "
"creatures, steal, commit adultery, lie, or encourage others to do the same. "
"Is that for their lasting welfare and happiness?”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc30"></a>
msgctxt "an3.65:30.1"
msgid "“Evaṃ, bhante”."
msgstr "“Yes, sir.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc31"></a>
msgctxt "an3.65:31.1"
msgid "“Taṃ kiṃ maññatha, kālāmā, "
msgstr "“What do you think, Kālāmas? "

msgctxt "an3.65:31.2"
msgid "adoso purisassa ajjhattaṃ uppajjamāno uppajjati … pe …"
msgstr "Does love come up in a person for their welfare or harm?"

msgctxt "an3.65:31.3"
msgid "amoho purisassa ajjhattaṃ uppajjamāno uppajjati … pe …"
msgstr "… Does understanding come up in a person for their welfare or harm?"

msgctxt "an3.65:31.4"
msgid "hitāya sukhāyā”ti."
msgstr "… Is that for their lasting welfare and happiness?”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc32"></a>
msgctxt "an3.65:32.1"
msgid "“Evaṃ, bhante”."
msgstr "“Yes, sir.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc33"></a>
msgctxt "an3.65:33.1"
msgid "“Taṃ kiṃ maññatha, kālāmā, ime dhammā kusalā vā akusalā vā”ti?"
msgstr "“What do you think, Kālāmas, are these things skillful or unskillful?”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc34"></a>
msgctxt "an3.65:34.1"
msgid "“Kusalā, bhante”."
msgstr "“Wholesome, sir.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc35"></a>
msgctxt "an3.65:35.1"
msgid "“Sāvajjā vā anavajjā vā”ti?"
msgstr "“Blameworthy or blameless?”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc36"></a>
msgctxt "an3.65:36.1"
msgid "“Anavajjā, bhante”."
msgstr "“Blameless, sir.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc37"></a>
msgctxt "an3.65:37.1"
msgid "“Viññugarahitā vā viññuppasatthā vā”ti?"
msgstr "“Criticized or praised by sensible people?”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc38"></a>
msgctxt "an3.65:38.1"
msgid "“Viññuppasatthā, bhante”."
msgstr "“Praised by sensible people, sir.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc39"></a>
msgctxt "an3.65:39.1"
msgid "“Samattā samādinnā hitāya sukhāya saṃvattanti no vā?"
msgstr ""
"“When you undertake them, do they lead to welfare and happiness, or not?"

msgctxt "an3.65:39.2"
msgid "Kathaṃ vā ettha hotī”ti?"
msgstr "Or how do you see this?”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc40"></a>
msgctxt "an3.65:40.1"
msgid "“Samattā, bhante, samādinnā hitāya sukhāya saṃvattanti."
msgstr "“When you undertake them, they lead to welfare and happiness."

msgctxt "an3.65:40.2"
msgid "Evaṃ no ettha hotī”ti."
msgstr "That’s how we see it.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pli1.192"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc41"></a>
msgctxt "an3.65:41.1"
msgid "“Iti kho, kālāmā, yaṃ taṃ avocumhā:"
msgstr "“So, Kālāmas, when we said:"

msgctxt "an3.65:41.2"
msgid "‘etha tumhe, kālāmā."
msgstr "‘Please,"

msgctxt "an3.65:41.3"
msgid ""
"Mā anussavena, mā paramparāya, mā itikirāya, mā piṭakasampadānena, mā "
"takkahetu, mā nayahetu, mā ākāraparivitakkena, mā diṭṭhinijjhānakkhantiyā, "
"mā bhabbarūpatāya, mā samaṇo no garūti."
msgstr ""
"don’t go by oral transmission, don’t go by lineage, don’t go by testament, "
"don’t go by canonical authority, don’t rely on logic, don’t rely on "
"inference, don’t go by reasoned contemplation, don’t go by the acceptance of "
"a view after consideration, don’t go by the appearance of competence, and "
"don’t think “The ascetic is our respected teacher.”"

msgctxt "an3.65:41.4"
msgid "Yadā tumhe, kālāmā, attanāva jāneyyātha—"
msgstr "But when you know for yourselves:"

msgctxt "an3.65:41.5"
msgid ""
"ime dhammā kusalā, ime dhammā anavajjā, ime dhammā viññuppasatthā, ime "
"dhammā samattā samādinnā hitāya sukhāya saṃvattantīti, atha tumhe, kālāmā, "
"upasampajja vihareyyāthā’ti, "
msgstr ""
"“These things are skillful, blameless, praised by sensible people, and when "
"you undertake them, they lead to welfare and happiness”, then you should "
"acquire them and keep them.’ "

msgctxt "an3.65:41.6"
msgid "iti yaṃ taṃ vuttaṃ idametaṃ paṭicca vuttaṃ."
msgstr "That’s what I said, and this is why I said it."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc42"></a>
#. VAR: Sa kho so → yo kho (mr)
#. VAR: patissato → sato (mr)
msgctxt "an3.65:42.1"
msgid ""
"Sa kho so, kālāmā, ariyasāvako evaṃ vigatābhijjho vigatabyāpādo asammūḷho "
"sampajāno patissato mettāsahagatena cetasā ekaṃ disaṃ pharitvā viharati, "
"tathā dutiyaṃ, tathā tatiyaṃ, tathā catutthaṃ, iti uddhamadho tiriyaṃ "
"sabbadhi sabbattatāya sabbāvantaṃ lokaṃ mettāsahagatena cetasā vipulena "
"mahaggatena appamāṇena averena abyāpajjhena pharitvā viharati."
msgstr ""
"Then that noble disciple is rid of desire, rid of ill will, unconfused, "
"aware, and mindful. They meditate spreading a heart full of love to one "
"direction, and to the second, and to the third, and to the fourth. In the "
"same way above, below, across, everywhere, all around, they spread a heart "
"full of love to the whole world—abundant, expansive, limitless, free of "
"enmity and ill will."

msgctxt "an3.65:42.2"
msgid "Karuṇāsahagatena cetasā … pe …"
msgstr ""
"They meditate spreading a heart full of compassion to one direction, and to "
"the second, and to the third, and to the fourth. In the same way above, "
"below, across, everywhere, all around, they spread a heart full of "
"compassion to the whole world—abundant, expansive, limitless, free of enmity "
"and ill will."

msgctxt "an3.65:42.3"
msgid "muditāsahagatena cetasā … pe …"
msgstr ""
"They meditate spreading a heart full of rejoicing to one direction, and to "
"the second, and to the third, and to the fourth. In the same way above, "
"below, across, everywhere, all around, they spread a heart full of rejoicing "
"to the whole world—abundant, expansive, limitless, free of enmity and ill "
"will."

msgctxt "an3.65:42.4"
msgid ""
"upekkhāsahagatena cetasā ekaṃ disaṃ pharitvā viharati, tathā dutiyaṃ, tathā "
"tatiyaṃ, tathā catutthaṃ, iti uddhamadho tiriyaṃ sabbadhi sabbattatāya "
"sabbāvantaṃ lokaṃ upekkhāsahagatena cetasā vipulena mahaggatena appamāṇena "
"averena abyāpajjhena pharitvā viharati."
msgstr ""
"They meditate spreading a heart full of equanimity to one direction, and to "
"the second, and to the third, and to the fourth. In the same way above, "
"below, across, everywhere, all around, they spread a heart full of "
"equanimity to the whole world—abundant, expansive, limitless, free of enmity "
"and ill will."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc43"></a>
#. VAR: Sa → sace (mr)
msgctxt "an3.65:43.1"
msgid ""
"Sa kho so, kālāmā, ariyasāvako evaṃ averacitto evaṃ abyāpajjhacitto evaṃ "
"asaṃkiliṭṭhacitto evaṃ visuddhacitto."
msgstr ""
"When that noble disciple has a mind that’s free of enmity and ill will, "
"uncorrupted and purified,"

msgctxt "an3.65:43.2"
msgid "Tassa diṭṭheva dhamme cattāro assāsā adhigatā honti."
msgstr "they’ve won four consolations in the present life."

#. VAR: sukatadukkaṭānaṃ → sukaṭadukkaṭānaṃ (bj, s1-3, km, pts1)
#. VAR: athāhaṃ → ṭhānamahaṃ (bj, pts1) | ṭhānametaṃ yenāhaṃ (s1-3, km)
msgctxt "an3.65:43.3"
msgid ""
"‘Sace kho pana atthi paro loko, atthi sukatadukkaṭānaṃ kammānaṃ phalaṃ "
"vipāko, athāhaṃ kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā sugatiṃ saggaṃ lokaṃ "
"upapajjissāmī’ti, ayamassa paṭhamo assāso adhigato hoti."
msgstr ""
"‘If it turns out there is another world, and good and bad deeds have a "
"result, then—when the body breaks up, after death—I’ll be reborn in a good "
"place, a heavenly realm.’ This is the first consolation they’ve won."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc44"></a>
#. VAR: athāhaṃ → idhāhaṃ (bj, s1-3, km, pts1)
#. VAR: sukhiṃ → sukhaṃ (bj) | sukhī (s1-3, km)
msgctxt "an3.65:44.1"
msgid ""
"‘Sace kho pana natthi paro loko, natthi sukatadukkaṭānaṃ kammānaṃ phalaṃ "
"vipāko, athāhaṃ diṭṭheva dhamme averaṃ abyāpajjhaṃ anīghaṃ sukhiṃ attānaṃ "
"pariharāmī’ti, ayamassa dutiyo assāso adhigato hoti."
msgstr ""
"‘If it turns out there is no other world, and good and bad deeds don’t have "
"a result, then in the present life I’ll keep myself free of enmity and ill "
"will, untroubled and happy.’ This is the second consolation they’ve won."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc45"></a>
msgctxt "an3.65:45.1"
msgid ""
"‘Sace kho pana karoto karīyati pāpaṃ, na kho panāhaṃ kassaci pāpaṃ cetemi."
msgstr ""
"‘If it turns out that bad things happen to people who do bad things, then "
"since I have no bad intentions,"

msgctxt "an3.65:45.2"
msgid ""
"Akarontaṃ kho pana maṃ pāpakammaṃ kuto dukkhaṃ phusissatī’ti, ayamassa "
"tatiyo assāso adhigato hoti."
msgstr ""
"and since I’m not doing anything bad, how can suffering touch me?’ This is "
"the third consolation they’ve won."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc46"></a>
msgctxt "an3.65:46.1"
msgid ""
"‘Sace kho pana karoto na karīyati pāpaṃ, athāhaṃ ubhayeneva visuddhaṃ "
"attānaṃ samanupassāmī’ti, ayamassa catuttho assāso adhigato hoti."
msgstr ""
"‘If it turns out that bad things don’t happen to people who do bad things, "
"then I still see myself pure on both sides.’ This is the fourth consolation "
"they’ve won."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc47"></a>
msgctxt "an3.65:47.1"
msgid ""
"Sa kho so, kālāmā, ariyasāvako evaṃ averacitto evaṃ abyāpajjhacitto evaṃ "
"asaṅkiliṭṭhacitto evaṃ visuddhacitto."
msgstr ""
"When that noble disciple has a mind that’s free of enmity and ill will, "
"undefiled and purified,"

msgctxt "an3.65:47.2"
msgid "Tassa diṭṭheva dhamme ime cattāro assāsā adhigatā hontī”ti."
msgstr "they’ve won these four consolations in the present life.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pli1.193"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc48"></a>
msgctxt "an3.65:48.1"
msgid "“Evametaṃ, bhagavā, evametaṃ, sugata."
msgstr "“That’s so true, Blessed One! That’s so true, Holy One!"

msgctxt "an3.65:48.2"
msgid ""
"Sa kho so, bhante, ariyasāvako evaṃ averacitto evaṃ abyāpajjhacitto evaṃ "
"asaṅkiliṭṭhacitto evaṃ visuddhacitto."
msgstr ""
"When that noble disciple has a mind that’s free of enmity and ill will, "
"undefiled and purified,"

msgctxt "an3.65:48.3"
msgid "Tassa diṭṭheva dhamme cattāro assāsā adhigatā honti."
msgstr "they’ve won these four consolations in the present life. …"

msgctxt "an3.65:48.4"
msgid ""
"‘Sace kho pana atthi paro loko, atthi sukatadukkaṭānaṃ kammānaṃ phalaṃ "
"vipāko, athāhaṃ kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā sugatiṃ saggaṃ lokaṃ "
"upapajjissāmī’ti, ayamassa paṭhamo assāso adhigato hoti."
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc49"></a>
msgctxt "an3.65:49.1"
msgid ""
"‘Sace kho pana natthi paro loko, natthi sukatadukkaṭānaṃ kammānaṃ phalaṃ "
"vipāko, athāhaṃ diṭṭheva dhamme averaṃ abyāpajjhaṃ anīghaṃ sukhiṃ attānaṃ "
"pariharāmī’ti, ayamassa dutiyo assāso adhigato hoti."
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc50"></a>
msgctxt "an3.65:50.1"
msgid ""
"‘Sace kho pana karoto karīyati pāpaṃ, na kho panāhaṃ kassaci pāpaṃ cetemi, "
"akarontaṃ kho pana maṃ pāpakammaṃ kuto dukkhaṃ phusissatī’ti, ayamassa "
"tatiyo assāso adhigato hoti."
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc51"></a>
msgctxt "an3.65:51.1"
msgid ""
"‘Sace kho pana karoto na karīyati pāpaṃ, athāhaṃ ubhayeneva visuddhaṃ "
"attānaṃ samanupassāmī’ti, ayamassa catuttho assāso adhigato hoti."
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc52"></a>
msgctxt "an3.65:52.1"
msgid ""
"Sa kho so, bhante, ariyasāvako evaṃ averacitto evaṃ abyāpajjhacitto evaṃ "
"asaṅkiliṭṭhacitto evaṃ visuddhacitto."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "an3.65:52.2"
msgid "Tassa diṭṭheva dhamme ime cattāro assāsā adhigatā honti."
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc53"></a>
msgctxt "an3.65:53.1"
msgid "Abhikkantaṃ, bhante … pe …"
msgstr "Excellent, sir! Excellent!"

msgctxt "an3.65:53.2"
msgid ""
"ete mayaṃ, bhante, bhagavantaṃ saraṇaṃ gacchāma dhammañca bhikkhusaṅghañca."
msgstr ""
"We go for refuge to Master Gotama, to the teaching, and to the mendicant "
"Saṅgha."

msgctxt "an3.65:53.3"
msgid "Upāsake no, bhante, bhagavā dhāretu ajjatagge pāṇupete saraṇaṃ gate”ti."
msgstr ""
"From this day forth, may the Buddha remember us as lay followers who have "
"gone for refuge for life.”"

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "an3.65:53.4"
msgid "Pañcamaṃ."
msgstr ""
